comment:
* PatternInfo class saves the first and second part of interval pattern,
     * and whether the interval pattern is earlier date first.

variables.name: fFirstDateInPtnIsLaterDate
variables.comment:
* Whether the first date in interval pattern is later date or not.
         * Fallback format set the default ordering.
         * And for a particular interval pattern, the order can be
         * overridden by prefixing the interval pattern with "latestFirst:" or
         * "earliestFirst:"
         * For example, given 2 date, Jan 10, 2007 to Feb 10, 2007.
         * if the fallback format is "{0} - {1}",
         * and the pattern is "d MMM - d MMM yyyy", the interval format is
         * "10 Jan - 10 Feb, 2007".
         * If the pattern is "latestFirst:d MMM - d MMM yyyy",
         * the interval format is "10 Feb - 10 Jan, 2007"

methods.name: public String getFirstPart()
methods.comment:
* Returns the first part of interval pattern.
         * @return The first part of interval pattern.

methods.name: public String getSecondPart()
methods.comment:
* Returns the second part of interval pattern.
         * @return The second part of interval pattern.

methods.name: public boolean firstDateInPtnIsLaterDate()
methods.comment:
* Returns whether the first date in interval patter is later date or not.
         * @return Whether the first date in interval patter is later date or not.

methods.name: public boolean equals(Object a)
methods.comment: * Compares the specified object with this PatternInfo for equality. * @param a The object to be compared. * @return true if the specified object is equal to this PatternInfo.

methods.name: public int hashCode()
methods.comment: * Returns the hash code of this PatternInfo. * @return A hash code value for this object.
